text:
If anyone had any of these experiences, please leave a response or +1.  
Too many issues to write about in detail but in summary
1/  I had 2 items, both valued at over $2K damaged at the hands of VC "quality"; several VC operational system errors regarding shipping confirmation, causing them to dismiss paying me my commission until I proactively chased the payment for 3 month (item has still not been properly tagged as shipped);
2/  HORRIBLE customer service and management, who have repeatedly ignored or overlooked many of my messages; 
3/  ridiculous seller fees, especially when they are negligently mishandling inventory and providing unscrupulous customer service; 
4/  mislabeled my seller profiles, causing my profile to decrease in the search and potentially lose sales (see example of my latest message to VC)
5/  Errors in the shipping and delivery system, which does not record or indicate real-world accuracy.  A couple of items sat in quality control for weeks, causing a disgruntled buyer to contact me and eventually I spent hours trying to rectify the situation.  As I observed, the buyer's process is also an issue as noted by several of my buyers.  With the example below, it literally took me at least 5 communications and ~3 months to receive my money for a blouse, which was clearly marked as shipped by Fed Ex, yet VC didn't seem to believe the item was shipped to the buyer and despite the tracking information validating the delivery, they waited for the buyer to approve receipt vs documents submitted by their "trusted seller".

April 4, 2021
Re: Expert vs Trusted Seller

I'd like to escalate my message to a supervisor, as this is not the first time I am contacting VC as a disgruntled seller. In fact, it seems like there is a huge issue on the operation side of the business and as many times  as I have messaged "customer service", I am in disbelief there there is no resolution or attention to my account.   According to the policy I am I am due to be an expert seller ad as I reviewed my stats, the sales/conformity stats are not accurate.  For instance, I sold a Dolce & Gabbana blouse earlier in the year and it was not credited for 3 months as the shipping and delivery system does not seem to indicate real-world accuracy.  It literally took me at least 5 communications and ~3 months to receive my money as VC didn't seem to believe the item was shipped to the buyer and despite the tracking information validating the delivery.  I have countless other issues in which the "quality team mishandled my items, many of which were worth thousands of dollars.   In doing the math and tallying the statistics,  I am due to be an expert seller (months ago) and would like to understand why this is not reflected in my profile.   I'm going to deal with one issue at a time but the VC model is subpar to many of its competitors and has caused me to halt on uploading 100s of items I have in inventory.

There are thousands of replicas being sold on this website, the quality check team doesn’t know what they are doing. I follow some accounts where people sell 100,200,300 fake items. I reported these people to Vestiaire but they really don’t care. Items such as 3000$ Bottega Veneta bags or 2000€ Max Mara coats from the best replicas factories are being sold on VC and they just do not care. They are replicas of brands such as orseund Iris, realisation, zimmermann, dion lee, nanushka, ganni, alexander wang, isabel marant, off white, self project, maison margiela, loewe, and many many more - all those people sell those items and their quality team thinks that they aren’t fakes of these brands and accept everything. I offered them my help, to join the team to help solving the replicas problems but they do not care. So I’m going to expose them. Here’s a list of profiles where people sell only counterfeit items from best replicas sellers (they got the info from Reddit from fashionreps or repladies) : ask these sellers for proof of purchase of anything - You won’t get any. 
@elera9686101 - over 120 fake items 
@noah11371357 - 50 items sold and 30 for sale. This girl is selling fakes for two years and has multiple accounts - when I contacted VC a year ago about it they confirmed it and deleted all the accounts, but she keeps getting new and i report them and they dont care. 
@filippapepp - also her account, here she’s selling a lot of bottega Veneta bags without invoice etc obviously fake and they accept it!!
@staplefindsuk - another fake seller
@tsf - 62 items sold. 150 for sale she’s even „proffesional seller”. She even uses pictures from Chinese rep sellers - try image searching them on Google and see what you’ll find. 
@oceanbeyond - fake bags, same story with photos taken from replicas sellers
@omega10951801 - fake items all of them
@alexander9983054 - 50 replicas sold, some worth over 2000€ I think they banned this account but I doubt they refunded and contacted every single buyer. 
@wendy5863 - all items are fake. 
@marcin12175320 - all fake so bad fakes. 
@julia10989919 same person as above
@michal8272504 same person as above
@wojtek9726526 same person as above
@kacper11182107 same person as above
And they are many more. If You look for these accounts you’ll see what I mean - they all sell the same brands, the same items; for low prices (because they buy cheap fakes). Vestiaire won’t care but most of these sellers lost trusted seller badges so that means they already have at least one item declared counterfeit - Vestiaire should delete these accounts forever - yet they decide to keep them online. They are tragic and pathetic. They only care about the money and until the buyer finds out they bought a fake they really don’t care.
